This weapon is designed to be usable at all ranges of combat, against all infantry targets.

-For fighting targets at long ranges, it is recommended that you raise your velocity to

-For fast moving/jumping targets use Stages 3-4 with an active lead. The higher stages

 and will allow you to conserve your ammunition.

 and cuts the weapon's lag down to very low levels.

-For fighting armored targets, use Stages 2-3 while sweeping constant fire across a large
 portion of the target. This allows you to send very large amounts of ammunition at the
 target without overloading the collision detection system in the armor, making most if
 not all of your shots count towards the destruction of the target.

-Using quick, controlled bursts will allow you to conserve ammuntition while decreasing
 physics lag. This is a recommended tactic, and it will save you from having to reload as
 often.
